events.name: Boston Celtics at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 23 points and the Boston Celtics rebounded from back-to-back losses to Atlanta, pulling away in the third quarter for a 104-92 win over the New Orleans Pelicans on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 23 as Celtics rebound from back-to-back losses with 104-92 win over Pelicans

headlines.description: — Wendell Carter Jr. had 15 points and 13 rebounds, Jalen Suggs and Cole Anthony added 15 points each and the Orlando Magic broke a three-game losing streak with a 118-88 rout of the Memphis Grizzlies on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Orlando Magic snap 3-game skid with 118-88 rout of Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had six dunks while scoring 36 points and the Milwaukee Bucks overcame Bogdan Bogdanovic's 38 points to beat Atlanta 122-113 on Saturday night, ending the Hawks' four-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giannis Antetokounmpo has 36 points, 16 rebounds to power Bucks past Hawks, 122-113
